  "prompt": "How is Bhagavad Geeta relevant in real life?",
  "response": "The Bhagavad Gita offers several relevant life lessons and philosophies:\n\n1. Professional Life\n- Emphasizes duty (dharma) and performing work without attachment to results\n- Teaches focus on effort rather than outcome\n- Encourages professional integrity and commitment\n\n2. Emotional Management\n- Provides strategies for managing stress and anxiety\n- Teaches detachment and emotional balance\n- Helps develop mental resilience\n\n3. Personal Growth\n- Promotes self-awareness and self-improvement\n- Encourages continuous learning and self-discipline\n- Advocates understanding one's inner potential\n\n4. Decision Making\n- Offers guidance on making ethical choices\n- Teaches importance of rational thinking\n- Helps distinguish between right and wrong\n\n5. Spiritual Development\n- Explains karma and life's purpose\n- Provides insights into self-realization\n- Promotes understanding of universal principles\n\n6. Conflict Resolution\n- Teaches peaceful problem-solving\n- Advocates non-violence and compassion\n- Encourages understanding different perspectives\n\n7. Leadership Principles\n- Provides leadership insights\n- Emphasizes selfless service\n- Promotes balanced and principled leadership\n\n8. Mental Health\n- Offers techniques for managing negative emotions\n- Promotes inner peace and meditation\n- Helps develop positive thinking\n\nThe Gita provides timeless wisdom applicable across various life situations.",
